# text = انا متكلمون الان فى صناعة الشعرا وانواعها ومخبرون اى قوة لكل واحد واحد منها وعلى اى سبيل ينبغى ان تتقوم الاسمار والاشعار ان كانت الفواسس مزمعة بان يجرى امرها مجرى الجودة وايضا من كم جزو هى وايما هى اجزاوها وكذلك نتكلم من اجل كم التى هى موجودة التى هى لها بعينها [ونتكلم] ونحن متكلمون فى هذا كله من حيث نبتدى اولا من الاشيا الاوايل
# transliteration = innā mutakallimūna al-āna fī ṣināʿati al-shuʿarāʾi wa-anwāʿihā wa-mukhbirūna ayya quwwatin li-kulli wāḥidin wāḥidin minhā wa-ʿalā ayyi sabīlin yanbaghī an tataqawwama al-asmāru wa-l-ashʿāru in kānat al-fawāsis muzmiʿatan bi-an yajriya amruhā majrā al-jūdati wa-ayḍan min kam juzʾin hiya wa-ayyumā hiya ajzāʾuhā wa-kadhālika natakallamu min ajli kam allatī hiya mawjūdatun allatī hiya lahā bi-ʿaynihā [wa-natakallamu] wa-naḥnu mutakallimūna fī hādhā kullihī min ḥaythu nabtadiʾu awwalan min al-ashyāʾi al-awāʾili
# prose_translation = We are now speaking of the art of the poets and its kinds, and reporting what power belongs to each one of them and in what way the tales and the poems must be constituted if the poiesis is set to run the course of excellence; and also of how many parts it consists and which its parts are; and likewise we speak of how many those [features] are that exist and that belong to it in itself; [and we speak] and — we speaking of all this — inasmuch as we begin first from the first things.
# literal_translation = Verily-we [are] speaking now in the-art of-the-poets and-its-kinds, and-reporting which power to-each one one of-them, and-upon which way it-is-necessary that be-constituted the-tales and-the-poems, if was the-fawāsis resolved by-that runs its-affair the-course of-the-excellence; and-also of how-many part it [is], and-which they [are] its-parts; and-likewise we-speak on-account-of how-many those-which they [are] existent, those-which they [are] to-it in-its-self; [and-we-speak] and-we [are] speaking in this all-of-it, from where we-begin firstly from the-things the-first.
